        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>The following are my personal views, and may, or may not be 100% accurate, but these are my feelings on the subject.</P><P><BR>The real problem with E-bay isn't whether it's right, or wrong, but whether it is legal or not.</P><P>Everyone who owns an account, pays money to keep the account and to play the game, they are paying for this "service" and in return, being able to log on and have access to play the game, Verant is fulfilling their end of the agreement by "delivering" this service.</P><P>Paying real moeny for items in the game (when the legal payment for the service has already been fulfilled) falls along the lines of being illegal, it is illegal to sell for real money, something that is not real, tangible, or a service.</P><P>Since each account holder is already payig for the service, buying other accounts through those not authorized to sell them, or items that are not real, or tangible, is in actuality breaking the law.</P><P></P><P>Kiluudar Ravenwind  57 Defiler,  Fennin Ro,   T'kagi Ro</font></td>
